Decorating a Christmas tree is a tradition most of us associate with glitter, jolly Santa figures and shining baubles – unless, of course, you happen to be Norwegian.

The country’s US Embassy has adorned their tree in honour of Edvard Munch’s ‘The Scream’.

Their annual Christmas tree at Washington’s Union Station features hundreds of the wailing man from Norway’s most famous painting.

