The embassy has been responsible for decorating the tree for the 16th year in a row.

The unusual ornaments have been commissioned especially to celebrate the 150th anniversary of the birth of Norwegian artist.

Each year the tree follows a theme and this year Norway celebrates one of its most famous sons.

More than 700 ornaments hang on the tree branches, each of them a tiny ‘screaming man’ reflector, making the Christmas tree shine even brighter as they echo the lights of the station.

‘In a way, it symbolizes all the angst in preparing for an excellent Christmas,’ Ambassador Kåre Aas told the Washington Post.

‘I, myself, have that feeling. I’m not the only one who wants to scream from time to time.’

